'''Gijinka''' (擬人化) is a [[Japanese]] word meaning "humanoid", "personification", or "[[anthropomorphism|anthropomorphic]]", although the use of the word outside of [[Japan]] has come to be slightly different from the use of the word "[[anthropomorphic]]" in the [[anime]]/[[manga]]/[[furry]]/etc community. Rather than referring to just any animal with human characteristics, a gijinka is most often a [[fan (aficionado)|fan]] re-design of an animal-like character from an [[animation]] or [[graphic novel]] in a human or humanoid form, (ex: a [[Digimon]] or [[Pokemon]]) or of a humanoid version of the artist's own original animal-like character.


[http://img.photobucket.com/albums/v342/NuriKitsune/permanent/gijinkaGatomon.jpg Gatomon] from the [[Digimon]] series and her gijinka counterpart. Artist unknown.

